OL,3,CConcerns over 'ridiculous' payout for
OL,4,CHampshire infected blood victims
OL,6,FConcerns have been raised over the
OL,7,F"ridiculous" compensation payment
OL,8,Fproposed for people who were the
OL,9,Fvictims of unethical research,
OL,10,Fincluding boys who were infected with
OL,11,FHIV and hepatitis as schoolchildren.
OL,13,FMore than #2 billion has now been paid
OL,14,Fin compensation to victims of the
OL,15,Finfected blood scandal.
OL,17,FBut a charity has raised "profound
OL,18,Fconcerns" about an element of the
OL,19,Fpayouts for people who were victims of
OL,20,F"unethical research".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/11
