OL,3,CConcerns over 'ridiculous' payout for
OL,4,CHampshire infected blood victims
OL,6,FDuring the 1970s and 1980s, the Lord
OL,7,FMayor's Treloar's College in Hampshire
OL,8,Foffered specialist care for children
OL,9,Fwith haemophilia.
OL,11,FPupils undergoing treatment for the
OL,12,Fdisorder were experimented on without
OL,13,Ftheir knowledge by NHS clinicians, who
OL,14,Fknew the dangers it posed.
OL,16,FThe Infected Blood Public Inquiry's
OL,17,Freport, published in May 2024, said
OL,18,Fthat children with bleeding disorders
OL,19,Fwho attended the school were treated
OL,20,Fas "objects for research" and were
OL,21,Fgiven "multiple, riskier" treatments.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/11
